description:
Welcome to...

The Museum ofJewish Beards!


























but.disabled = false;
dir = 'img/people/';
r = 0;
text = new Array(
"Jewish patriarchs, such as <b>Abraham</b> and <b>Moses</b>, are always portrayed with full, bushy beards. Life was not easy in the desert heat.",
"<b>Jesus Christ</b> and his apostles (pictured: <b>Saint Peter</b>) are always shown bearded as well. But we'll let the obviously more pathetic Museum of Christian Beards handle their facial hair.",
"Through the centuries, beard styles changed. Compare the impeccably groomed beard of <b>Maimonides</b> (12th c.) to the lengthiness of <b>Nostradamus</b> (16th c.)",
"The <i>van dyke</i> proved to be a popular alternative for both artistic and adventurous types. Here we see it sported by painter <b>Diego Velazquez</b> (17th c.) and pirate <b>Jean Lafitte</b> (18th c.)",
"The 19th century brought a rebirth of the heavy beard movement. Here we see artist <b>Camille Pissarro</b>, in a self-portrait, and chess champion <b>Wilhelm Steinitz</b> recall the time of the patriarchs.",
"We also began to see the mustacheless beard make an appearance, here on the faces of politician <b>Judah P. Benjamin</b> and blue jeans inventor <b>Levi Strauss</b>.",
"No beard museum would be complete without the magnificent growths of philosopher <b>Karl Marx</b> and New Zealand president <b>Julius Vogel</b>. Truly, the 19th century was the Jewish beard's golden age!",
"The 20th century saw a worldwide beard revolution. The avant-garde artist <b>Man Ray</b> gave us the amazing half-beard, while muttonchopped author <b>Isaac Asimov</b> made us ponder, where do sideburns end and the beard begins?",
"Nowadays, there are all kinds of options. Some, such as anthropologist <b>Claude Levi-Strauss</b> and director <b>Steven Spielberg</b>, went with the classy, neatly trimmed look.",
"While others, such as beatnik poet <b>Allen Ginsberg</b> and mathematician <b>Grigory Perelman</b>, let it all loose.",
"The <i>goatee</i> became a popular choice. For unknown reasons, it is often sported by douchebags, here represented by child actor <b>Dustin Diamond</b> and sports talk show host <b>Jim Rome</b>.",
"Can Jewish women be bearded? Yes, and it is no laughing matter. Here we have half-Jewish sideshow performer <b>Jane Barnell</b> and sort-of-Jewish college professor (and sideshow performer, natch) <b>Jennifer Miller</b>.",
"We hope our tour has been informative! We leave you with the wackiness of comedian <b>Yakov Smirnoff</b> and the weirdness of (half Jewish) actor <b>Joaquin Phoenix</b>. May your own beards be as wonderful!"
);
pic = new Array(
"a/abraham", "m/moses",
"j/jesus_christ", "s/saint_peter",
"m/maimonides", "n/nostradamus",
"d/diego_velazquez", "../other/lafitte",
"c/camille_pissarro", "w/wilhelm_steinitz",
"j/judah_p__benjamin", "l/levi_strauss",
"k/karl_marx", "j/julius_vogel",
"m/man_ray", "i/isaac_asimov",
"c/claude_levi-strauss", "s/steven_spielberg",
"a/allen_ginsberg", "g/grigory_perelman",
"d/dustin_diamond", "j/jim_rome",
"../other/bearded_lady1", "../other/bearded_lady2",
"y/yakov_smirnoff", "j/joaquin_phoenix"
);
function begin() {
welcome.style.display = 'none';
museum.style.display = 'inline';
next();
}
function url(r,k) {
x = r*2+k;
return dir + pic[x] + ".jpg"
}
function show(r) {
pic1.src = url(r,0);
pic2.src = url(r,1);
}
function next() {
but.value = 'Next';
show(r);
note.innerHTML = text[r];
r++;
if (r == text.length) {
but.value = 'Restart Tour';
r = 0;
}
}
